    "created_at": "2015-05-19T07:26:12Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-05-19T07:26:12Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I don't think this is a good idea.  Our low level engine code is designed to ask questions (via interfaces) about what a unit _does_ (\"can I be targeted\", \"am I visible\") instead of what it _is_ (\"am I cloaked\"), which then comes will a pile of mod-specific baggage about what that means.\n\nIt looks like your motivation for this was to work around issues with the GPS satellite, which is the perfect example of people not having followed the rule above.  Adding yet more code in the same vein might fix the symptoms, but it makes the underlying problem even worse.\n"
  },
